07/04/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Central Bank Governor Radovan Jelasic's resignation has been accepted by the National Bank of Serbia's council, local media reported Tuesday (April 6th). 
Ruling coalition parties have reportedly struck a deal on his replacement, though any nomination requires a formal proposal by parliament's finance committee and is subject to approval by MPs. 
Jelasic tendered his resignation on March 23rd, citing personal reasons. 
(Beta, RTS, B92 - 06/04/10)
